<BaseLayout title="LS Academy | Franco Lopez" description="LS Academy is an in-progress Kubernetes-hosted learning platform for dealer training and enablement.">
  <header class="page-header">
    <span class="eyebrow">current build · kubernetes-hosted</span>
    <h1>LS Academy</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A Kubernetes-hosted learning platform for dealer training, enablement, and internal education.
    </p>
  </header>

  <article class="content">
    <h2>Problem</h2>
    <p>
      Dealer training needs a platform that can scale beyond one-off documents and manual delivery.
      The goal is to make training easier to publish, access, maintain, and measure.
    </p>

    <h2>What I’m building</h2>
    <p>
      LS Academy is an in-progress learning platform hosted on Kubernetes for roughly 350-500+ users.
      The work includes application hosting, deployment workflows, access patterns, platform operations,
      and practical reliability concerns.
    </p>

    <h2>Why it matters for my career direction</h2>
    <p>
      This project shows current momentum. It is not a historical bullet from years ago. It is where I’m
      actively applying Kubernetes, cloud infrastructure, deployment thinking, and platform operations.
    </p>

    <h2>What I’m watching closely</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Simple deployment and rollback paths</li>
      <li>Clear ownership of app, data, and infrastructure layers</li>
      <li>User access and administrative workflows</li>
      <li>Documentation that makes the platform easier to operate later</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
